GenOn Energy, Inc.: Private Company Information - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 24, 2017 4:21 PM ET
Independent Power and Renewable Electricity Producers

Company Overview of GenOn Energy, Inc.



Snapshot People




Company Overview
GenOn Energy, Inc., a wholesale generator, owns and operates power generation facilities primarily in the United States. It generates electricity using natural gas, coal, and oil resources. The company also trades in energy, capacity, and related products; and transacts and trades in fuel and transportation services. It has approximately 16,423 megawatts of net electric generating capacity. The company was founded in 1982 and is based in Princeton, New Jersey. GenOn Energy, Inc. is a subsidiary of NRG Energy, Inc. On June 14, 2017, GenOn Energy, Inc., along with affiliates, filed a voluntary petition for reorganization under Chapter 11 in the US Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of ...
GenOn Energy, Inc., a wholesale generator, owns and operates power generation facilities primarily in the United States. It generates electricity using natural gas, coal, and oil resources. The company also trades in energy, capacity, and related products; and transacts and trades in fuel and transportation services. It has approximately 16,423 megawatts of net electric generating capacity. The company was founded in 1982 and is based in Princeton, New Jersey. GenOn Energy, Inc. is a subsidiary of NRG Energy, Inc. On June 14, 2017, GenOn Energy, Inc., along with affiliates, filed a voluntary petition for reorganization under Chapter 11 in the US Bankruptcy Court for the Southern District of Texas.
Detailed Description


