GenOn Energy, Inc. Key Developments

Reorganization Plan and Disclosure Statement Filed by GenOn Energy, Inc.
Jun 29 17
GenOn Energy, Inc. filed a joint plan of reorganization and related disclosure statement in the US Bankruptcy Court on June 29, 2017. Under the plan, the administrative claims, LC facility claims, professional fee claims and priority tax claims will be paid in full in cash. The other secured claims and other priority claims will payment in full either in cash, delivery of collateral securing any such Claim and payment of any interest required under section 506(b) of the Bankruptcy Code or reinstatement of the claim. Revolving Credit Facility claims of $268.5 million consists of approximately $124.9 million in cash borrowings and $143.6 million of letters of credit will receive payment in full in Cash in accordance with the NRG Settlement. GenOn Notes claims of approximately $1.87 billion in principal outstanding on three series of GenOn Notes will receive 100% of the New Common Stock, the GenOn Notes Cash Pool amount of $75 million and the Subscription Rights in full satisfaction of the claim. GAG Notes claims of approximately $704.8 million in principal outstanding on two series of GAG Notes will receive cash in an amount equal to 92% of the principal amount and accrued interest as of the Petition Date and its Pro Rata share of the GAG Notes Cash Pool amount of $14.1 million. General Unsecured claims will receive payment in cash in an amount equal to such Allowed General Unsecured claim. Intercompany Claims and Interests will either be Reinstated or canceled and released at the option of the Debtors, with the consent of the GenOn Steering Committee. Section 510(b) claims will be cancelled and there shall be no distribution to Holders of Section 510(b) Claims. Interests in GenOn will be cancelled, released, and extinguished, and will be of no further force or effect. The plan will be funded from cash on hand, issuance and distribution of the New Common Stock and Exit Financing and New Secured Notes Offering.


GenOn Energy Sells $550 Million of Senior Notes
May 10 17
GenOn Energy Inc., through Remote Escrow Finance Vehicle LLC, on May 8 completed the sale of $550 million of its 10.5% senior secured first-lien notes due June 1, 2022. Proceeds from the offering will be deposited in a segregated escrow account until satisfaction of certain conditions. Upon satisfaction of said conditions, the NRG Energy Inc. subsidiary will merge with the initial issuer and assume all obligations under the notes. GenOn will then use net proceeds, together with cash on hand, to redeem or discharge outstanding 7.875% senior notes due 2017. Interest on the notes is payable semiannually on June 1 and Dec. 1, starting Dec. 1.


GenOn Energy, Inc. Announces Proposed Offering of Senior Secured First Lien Notes
May 4 17
GenOn Energy, Inc. announced that it intends to commence an offering of $540 million in aggregate principal amount of senior secured first lien notes due 2022. The New Notes will be senior first-priority secured obligations of GenOn and will be guaranteed by its existing and future restricted subsidiaries that guarantee the company's existing revolving credit facility. The New Notes will be initially issued by a special purpose limited liability company, which will not be an affiliate of the company, and the proceeds of the offering will be deposited in a segregated escrow account until the date on which certain escrow conditions are satisfied and the escrow proceeds are released (the “Escrow Conditions”). Concurrent with the satisfaction of the Escrow Conditions, the Escrow Issuer will merge with and into GenOn and GenOn will be the surviving entity and assume all of the obligations of the Escrow Issuer under the notes and the indenture governing the notes by operation of law. The New Notes will be subject to a special mandatory redemption if the Escrow Conditions are not satisfied or if GenOn, in its sole discretion, otherwise determines to redeem the New Notes on or prior to June 14, 2017. The New Notes and related guarantees are being offered only in the United States to qualified institutional buyers in reliance on Rule 144A under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended (the “Securities Act”), and outside the United States in offshore transactions to non-U.S. persons in compliance with Regulation S under the Securities Act. The New Notes and related guarantees have not been registered under the Securities Act or the securities laws of any other jurisdiction and may not be offered or sold in the United States absent registration or an applicable exemption from the registration requirements. This notice is issued pursuant to Rule 135c under the Securities Act, and does not constitute an offer to sell, or a solicitation of an offer to purchase, the New Notes.


